{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":37702,"name":"","username":"Lys0gen","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/57b2e6/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-05-18T20:53:48.445Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello, I have encountered a weird issue.\u003cbr\u003e\nI tried 3 fonts - Arial, Times New Roman and Tahoma - and with all of them the UI fails to display a simple minus sign. Perhaps there is an issue with other characters as well, but this was most glaring as I can’t display negative numbers. There is no whitespace or anything, the text is just shown as if there is nothing there. Escaping it did not do anything either.\u003cbr\u003e\nNote that \u003cstrong\u003eit does work with the default UI’s “Anonymous Pro” font\u003c/strong\u003e but that is not really a solution for me.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyone have an idea why this happens?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-05-18T20:53:48.445Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":47,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":244.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6163,"topic_slug":"ui-not-displaying-minus-sign-with-most-fonts","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1317,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37705,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-05-19T01:20:56.639Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhich minus sign? If it’s an en or em dash I could see it being that the font doesn’t allo the non-ASCII character by default. I have no idea if that’s the actual cause, I just think it might be a possibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEdit: I tried it myself with Arial and I couldn’t get the “-” to display without using font size 64. Hopefully someone more knowlegable can help, as that seems to be a serious problem.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-05-19T01:44:56.742Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":9.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6163,"topic_slug":"ui-not-displaying-minus-sign-with-most-fonts","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37706,"name":"Yao Wei Tjong","username":"weitjong","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/{size}/4_2.png","created_at":"2020-05-19T02:24:59.783Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eCould you log it as a bug in the issue tracker. Hopefully GitHub will suggest the person who last contributed the code for TTF rendering and you can ping him. I can’t recall his name off hand now.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-05-19T02:24:59.783Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":14.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6163,"topic_slug":"ui-not-displaying-minus-sign-with-most-fonts","display_username":"Yao Wei Tjong","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Admin","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":4,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":37811,"name":"","username":"Lumak","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/8491ac/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-06-02T00:19:34.361Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI was surprised about the ‘-’ char code missing in arial.ttf and I looked into this bug. The bug lies in FreeType lib.\u003cbr\u003e\ncode that Urho3D calls are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e FT_Get_First_Char(face, \u0026amp;glyphIndex);\nand \ncharCode = FT_Get_Next_Char(face, charCode, \u0026amp;glyphIndex);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand no where from the 1st call to the last is ‘-’ returned, eventhough, that charcode exists. FreeType is now 2.10 something and might have that fix.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTemporary fix would be to add at\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"onebox githubblob\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/FontFaceFreeType.cpp#L219\" target=\"_blank\"\u003egithub.com\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/FontFaceFreeType.cpp#L219\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eurho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/FontFaceFreeType.cpp#L219\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cpre class=\"onebox\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-cpp\"\u003e\u003col class=\"start lines\" start=\"209\" style=\"counter-reset: li-counter 208 ;\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    unsigned charCode = charCodes[i];\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    if (charCode == 0)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        continue;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e    if (!LoadCharGlyph(charCode, image))\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    {\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        hasMutableGlyph_ = true;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e        break;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    }\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e}\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli class=\"selected\"\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eSharedPtr\u0026lt;Texture2D\u0026gt; texture = LoadFaceTexture(image);\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eif (!texture)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e    return false;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003etextures_.Push(texture);\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003efont_-\u0026gt;SetMemoryUse(font_-\u0026gt;GetMemoryUse() + textureWidth * textureHeight);\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e// Store kerning if face has kerning information\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eif (FT_HAS_KERNING(face))\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e{\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eat L 219\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\tif (!LoadCharGlyph('-', image))\n\t{\n\t\thasMutableGlyph_ = true;\n\t}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePic or it didn’t happen?\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://i.imgur.com/xfINWNf.png\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.imgur.com/xfINWNf.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#fa